    {
      "instruction": "<p>Slice your <strong>brioche bun[s] </strong>in half</p><p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) (or griddle if you have one), over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>brioche halves</strong>, cut-side down, and cook for 3 min or until toasted and charred, then set them aside until serving</p><p>Tip: Cooking for 3 or more? You may need to do this in 2 batches!</p><p>Grate your <strong>cheddar cheese</strong></p>",
      "order": 6,
